From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steven Lamphear <steven@stevenlamphear.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] staging: rtl8723cs: fix CFI signature of rtw_xmit_entry

rtw_xmit_entry is assigned to net_device_ops::ndo_start_xmit, whose
expected signature is

  netdev_tx_t (*)(struct sk_buff *, struct net_device *)

but the staging driver declares it returning int. After typedef
expansion the parameter types already match (_pkt is struct sk_buff
and _nic_hdl is struct net_device *), so the only mismatch is the
return type.

With kCFI enabled on arm64, the indirect call from dev_hard_start_xmit
hashes the expected target type and traps when it does not match,
producing a fatal panic on the PinePhone as soon as wpa_supplicant
sends a frame:

  CFI failure at dev_hard_start_xmit+0xdc/0x250
   (target: rtw_xmit_entry+0x0/0xd4 [8723cs];
    expected type: 0xc4815b0f)
  Kernel panic - not syncing: Oops - CFI: Fatal exception in interrupt

Change the return type of rtw_xmit_entry (and its forward declaration
in the PLATFORM_LINUX block of xmit_osdep.h) to netdev_tx_t so the
CFI type hash matches, and update the local `ret` variable to use
netdev_tx_t / NETDEV_TX_OK to match.

Link: https://gitlab.postmarketos.org/postmarketOS/pmaports/-/work_items/4507
---
 drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/include/xmit_osdep.h      | 2 +-
 drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/os_dep/linux/xmit_linux.c | 4 ++--
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/include/xmit_osdep.h b/drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/include/xmit_osdep.h
--- a/drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/include/xmit_osdep.h
+++ b/drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/include/xmit_osdep.h
@@ -68,7 +68,7 @@
 struct xmit_buf;
 
 extern int _rtw_xmit_entry(_pkt *pkt, _nic_hdl pnetdev);
-extern int rtw_xmit_entry(_pkt *pkt, _nic_hdl pnetdev);
+extern netdev_tx_t rtw_xmit_entry(_pkt *pkt, _nic_hdl pnetdev);
 
 #endif /* PLATFORM_LINUX */
 
diff --git a/drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/os_dep/linux/xmit_linux.c b/drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/os_dep/linux/xmit_linux.c
--- a/drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/os_dep/linux/xmit_linux.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/rtl8723cs/os_dep/linux/xmit_linux.c
@@ -510,11 +510,11 @@
 }
 #endif
 
-int rtw_xmit_entry(_pkt *pkt, _nic_hdl pnetdev)
+netdev_tx_t rtw_xmit_entry(_pkt *pkt, _nic_hdl pnetdev)
 {
 	_adapter *padapter = (_adapter *)rtw_netdev_priv(pnetdev);
 	struct	mlme_priv	*pmlmepriv = &(padapter->mlmepriv);
-	int ret = 0;
+	netdev_tx_t ret = NETDEV_TX_OK;
 
 	if (pkt) {
 #ifdef CONFIG_CUSTOMER_ALIBABA_GENERAL
-- 
